  "prompt": "What are the best Shahrukh khan movies?",
  "response": "Shah Rukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" has had a prolific career with numerous acclaimed films. Here are some of his best movies, spanning different genres:\n\n1. **Dilwale Dulhania Le Jayenge (1995)** - A classic romance that has become a cultural phenomenon in India, telling the story of Raj and Simran's love against familial opposition.\n\n2. **My Name Is Khan (2010)** - A powerful drama about a man with Asperger's syndrome who embarks on a journey across America to meet the President after a personal tragedy.\n\n3. **Chak De! India (2007)** - A sports drama where Khan plays a former hockey player who becomes the coach of the Indian women's national hockey team. It's an inspiring story of triumph and grit.\n\n4. **Kuch Kuch Hota Hai (1998)** - A beloved romantic drama that explores themes of friendship and love, featuring memorable music and performances.\n\n5. **Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham (2001)** - A family drama that delves into themes of love and familial ties, showcasing an ensemble cast that includes several Bollywood stars.\n\n6. **Devdas (2002)** - A tragic love story based on the novel of the same name, where Khan portrays a man who spirals into despair after losing the love of his life.\n\n7. **Swades (2004)** - A thought-provoking film about an NRI returning to India, exploring issues of rural development and national pride.\n\n8. **Baazigar (1993)** - A thriller where Khan plays a complex anti-hero, marking one of his early successful films that showcased his versatility.\n\n9. **Om Shanti Om (2007)** - A reincarnation drama-comedy that pays homage to the Bollywood film industry, noted for its lavish production and entertaining storyline.\n\n10. **Raees (2017)** - A gritty crime drama where Khan plays a bootlegger navigating the complexities of law and morality.\n\nThese films reflect Shah Rukh Khan's versatility as an actor and his ability to connect with audiences across various themes and genres.",
